               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-269-person1463">
                  ROBERT 
                  BOYD
               <interp inst="t18260406-269-person1463" type="surname" value="BOYD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-269-person1463" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-269-person1463" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a builder. I know where this lead was taken from - I afterwards saw it fitted - it tallied exactly; I have no doubt it came from there - the building belongs to John Smith and William Hill Stamp; on the 22d of March, about a quarter-past eight o'clock, I saw the prisoner and another person drawing a sack from the area of this carcass, and when they got it to the wall joining the side of the bank, I saw another youth heaving it on the prisoner's back; I pursued, and met him with the lead - the other escaped; the lead was gone from off the gutters of four houses - there were seven or eight hundred weight in all.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-269-person1464">
                  HUGH 
